# Component Registry and Bind-Point Model

The next architecture step is to open `derived_section` and `custom_section` so a client can select any supported component as the repeated row renderer, then bind datasource columns to documented component bind points.

Component definition shape:

- `type`: stable component key, for example `primitive.button`, `primitive.checkbox`, `primitive.div`, `primitive.image`, `compound.card`, or `custom.<id>`.
- `label`, `group`, `description`: display metadata for the builder picker.
- `repeatable`: whether the component can be used as a row renderer.
- `props_schema`: static component props that are edited once for the whole section.
- `style_targets`: stable class/part keys that accept style overrides.
- `bind_points`: named targets that can receive row data.
- `slots` or `children`: allowed nested primitive/compound composition behavior.
- `version`: schema version for migration and saved payload compatibility.

Bind-point definition shape:

- `key`: stable bind-point name such as `title`, `body`, `media`, `href`, `checked`, `disabled`, `icon`, `aria_label`, or `dataset`.
- `label` and `description`: builder-facing documentation.
- `kind`: data contract category such as `text`, `rich_text`, `number`, `boolean`, `url`, `media`, `image`, `video`, `object`, `array`, `action`, or `any`.
- `required`: whether the component needs this binding to render.
- `accepted_columns`: optional column type hints from datasource metadata.
- `validation`: JSON schema or compact backend validation rules.
- `fallback`: optional static value when no column is bound.
- `transform`: optional supported transform key for formatting, not arbitrary runtime code at first.

Saved section config should evolve toward:

- `datasource_id` or `custom_section_id` as today.
- `component_type`: selected registered component.
- `component_version`: version used when saved.
- `bindings`: map of bind-point key to datasource column path, literal value, object path, or transform.
- `row_key_column`: stable row identity for replication.
- `style_overrides`: map of component `style_targets` to allowed style properties.
- `row_overrides`: per-row overrides by row key.

Detection strategy:

- Prefer explicit component metadata for first-party primitives and compound components. This keeps validation predictable and avoids coupling core behavior to DOM shape.
- Add an inspector for custom HTML/custom components that detects semantic elements and emits proposed bind points:
  - text-capable nodes become `text`/`rich_text` candidates.
  - anchors become `text` plus `href`/`aria_label` candidates.
  - buttons become `text`, `disabled`, and optional action candidates.
  - checkboxes become `checked`, `disabled`, and label candidates.
  - images/video/player elements become `media`, `image`, `video`, `poster`, `alt`, and caption candidates.
  - containers become object/list/style target candidates when marked with data attributes.
- Detection output is only a draft contract. Saved custom components should persist an explicit generated definition so future renders and validation do not depend on re-inspecting arbitrary markup.
- Custom HTML should support optional `data-bind`, `data-bind-kind`, `data-style-target`, and `data-slot` attributes so clients can make detection precise.

Validation rules:

- Backend validation must reject unknown `component_type`s, unknown bind-point keys, incompatible datasource column/value types, missing required bind points, and unsafe style override properties.
- Frontend validation should mirror backend metadata for fast feedback, but backend remains authoritative.
- Complex datasource values must be supported through object paths and typed bind points, not just flat string columns.
- Media bind points must distinguish image, video, generic media object, and URL-only values.
- Link/action bind points must validate URL/action shape separately from display text.

Rendering rules:

- `derived_section` executes the datasource, resolves each row's configured bindings, validates/coerces values, and replicates the selected component per row.
- `custom_section` can reference a saved custom component/template and use the same binding contract.
- Primitive components should stay visually and behaviorally generic. Registry metadata and bind mappings decide how row data flows into them.
- Style overrides apply through registered `style_targets`; arbitrary inline CSS should remain constrained.

