# Frontend Primitive Consolidation Review

Reviewed 2026-05-29 against current `backend/frontend/src/components` and `backend/frontend/src/pages` usage.

Shared primitive direction:

- Prefer existing global CSS primitives before adding local component-specific UI: `.btn`, `.icon-btn`, `.badge`, `.card`, `.section`, `.form-group`, grid helpers, skeleton helpers, and semantic tokens in `index.css`.
- Add variants to these primitives instead of introducing one-off React wrappers or page-local button/badge/card classes when behavior is the same.
- Treat page blocks as composable UI building blocks for the registry-driven page system; block-specific classes should express layout/content differences, not duplicate primitive controls.
- Keep `components/ui/*` focused on genuinely reusable interactive primitives such as pickers and skeletons. Do not add new component families until a repeated pattern cannot be handled through the existing primitive classes.

Duplicate surfaces found:

- Buttons: many local families repeat primary, secondary, danger, warning, ghost, compact, and large button behavior (`GrengoDashboard`, `SecuritySettings`, user profile dialogs, store admin actions, error pages, page admin controls).
- Badges: local status badges repeat success, warning, error, info, enabled/disabled/running/stopped states.
- Empty/loading states: repeated `*-empty` classes should converge on one shared empty-state primitive when designs are aligned.
- Dialog/modal shells: forum, store, users, and admin dialogs repeat header/body/footer/close-button structure and should eventually share modal primitives.
- Form rows and field controls: `.form-group` is already the shared field primitive and should absorb generic input fixes such as checkbox sizing.

Completed primitive moves:

- Checkbox sizing reset now lives in `index.css` and `components/ui/FormGroup.css`.
- Button size and semantic variants now live in `index.css`: `.btn-sm`, `.btn-lg`, `.btn-block`, `.btn-ghost`, `.btn-danger`, `.btn-warning`.
- Badge semantic variants now live in `index.css`: `.badge-success`, `.badge-warning`, `.badge-error`, `.badge-info`.
- Route/work-surface primitives now live in `index.css`: `.page-shell`, `.page-header`, `.page-title`, `.page-subtitle`, `.ui-panel`, `.ui-toolbar`, `.ui-actions`, `.ui-tabs`, `.ui-tab`, `.ui-empty`, `.ui-dialog-overlay`, `.ui-dialog`, `.form-grid`, `.form-actions`, `.form-check`.
- `ErrorPage` uses shared `.btn` and `.ui-actions` instead of local error-button components.
- Store empty state uses shared `.ui-empty` with only store-specific adornment styles remaining.

Route CSS audit findings:

- Low-drift routes already using primitives: cart, forum category/view thread surfaces, datasource list cards, custom pages, several page blocks using `.card`, `.btn`, `.action-btn`, `.badge`, and skeleton helpers.
- Medium-drift routes should migrate local controls to primitives as touched: store admin actions, activity feed badges/empty states, resource analytics panel tabs/toolbar/empty state, notification panel buttons, data source editor tabs/toolbars/forms, roles management action rows and permission cards.
- High-drift route/components should be broken down before registry metadata work: `InboxPage`, `GrengoDashboard`, `UserProfile` plus profile subpanels, `SecuritySettings`, `PageBuilder`, `CardDesigner`, `TabbedEditor`, and integration blocks (`DataSourcesBlock`, `DerivedSectionBlock`, `CustomSectionBlock`, `CodeEditorBlock`). These files combine route orchestration, local primitives, data state, and repeated control patterns.

Modular UI system extraction targets:

- `RouteShell`: page header, title/subtitle, actions, toolbar, and empty state metadata.
- `ActionButton` / primitive class metadata: maps to `.btn`, `.action-btn`, semantic variants, sizes, disabled/loading state, and destructive action intent.
- `StatusBadge`: maps semantic status names to `.badge-*` variants for registry-driven status rendering.
- `DialogSurface`: overlay, shell, header/body/footer/action rows, close affordance, and fixed-width variants.
- `TabSurface`: tab list, tab button, active/error/warning badge, overflow behavior.
- `EditorField`: label, help text, input/select/textarea, checkbox row, grid layout, validation/error state.
- `DataDisplay`: table wrapper, card grid, preview card, empty/loading/error states for datasource and custom-section outputs.

Migration rule:

- Route and block CSS may keep domain-specific layout and content classes, but primitive-shaped UI (`button`, `badge`, `card`, `dialog`, `tabs`, `toolbar`, `empty`, `field`, `grid`) should first use shared primitive classes. If a route needs a new visual state, extend the primitive class catalog and document it here before adding another page-local family.

